@prefix sh: <http://www.w3.org/ns/shacl#> .
@prefix : <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/code#> .
@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix geo: <http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#> .
@prefix skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#> .
@prefix dcterms: <http://purl.org/dc/terms/> .
@prefix dcam: <http://purl.org/dc/dcam/> .
@prefix prov: <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#> .
@prefix trivyn: <http://trivyn.io/ontology#> .
@prefix obo: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/> .
@prefix cco: <https://www.commoncoreontologies.org/> .
@prefix se: <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/engineering#> .
@base <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/code#> .

<https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/code> a owl:Ontology ;
    rdfs:label "Software Code Layer" ;
    rdfs:comment "Code entities beneath the architectural component layer: the structural vocabulary the v2 code layer mints into the project knowledge graph. Hand-curated from a Trivyn pipeline generation; see skos:editorialNote." ;
    dcterms:created "2026-07-08T05:46:40Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    dcterms:modified "2026-07-08T07:30:00Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    dcterms:creator "Trivyn Ontology Pipeline" ;
    dcterms:publisher "Trivyn" ;
    owl:versionInfo "0.1.0" ;
    skos:editorialNote """Hand-curated 2026-07-08 (MOOSEDev v2 slice-2 Phase 0 session, james + claude-code) from the
Trivyn v0.8.4 generation of the full three-strata code-layer model. Curation decisions:
- v2.0 scope is CodeEntity only (five datatype properties + shape). The other ratified stratum
  classes are PARKED: declared for name stability, no properties or shapes until their stratum's
  machinery ships (judgments need the v2.1 ratification inbox; observations need v2.2 instrumentation).
- CodeEntity subclasses se:Component (ratified lineage, AD b0d3e4d9); the generator's
  arch:SystemComponent bridge was overruled — code entities must not be legal targets of
  component-only machinery (coversPath, component dossiers).
- Kind is a datatype property (hasEntityKind), not a class hierarchy: the kind taxonomy belongs
  to the index producer, not the ontology. The generated CodeKind class was dropped.
- The upward intent links (realizes / satisfies / embodies) are declared HERE — the code layer
  links upward into architecture, so the dependent module owns the bridge. The widenings of the
  architecture ontology's own generic predicates (concerns / constrains / violates) are
  necessarily in-place edits in software-architecture{,_shapes}.ttl. Generated duplicates of
  record-layer classes (Requirement, Pattern, Constraint, AntiPattern) and their properties were
  dropped: the store's relation machinery does not reason over owl:equivalentClass, so duplicates
  are drift, not reuse.
- Refactor continuity is deferred typed edges (renamedFrom / movedFrom / splitInto / mergedInto,
  AD 136dbf24), not an event class; the generated RefactorEvent was dropped.
- Generated alignments AuthorshipProvenance ⊑ se:ExternalDependency and CodeFile ⊑ se:Module were
  overruled (semantically wrong; files and modules are distinct containment hierarchies).""" ;
    dcterms:provenance """Generated by Trivyn v0.8.4 on 2026-07-08T05:46:40Z.
Sources: unknown sources.
Domain ontology: Software Engineering.
Domain hint: The source-code layer of a software system — the code entities beneath the architectural component layer, and the typed knowledge attached to them. Extends the existing software-engineering ontology (system, component, module, interface, data store); reuse its terms, do not remodel them. Language-agnostic: language specifics live in the code-index identity scheme, not here.

Core concepts: code entity (a continuant identified by symbol path plus kind — function, method, type, trait, macro, const, test, migration, config — persisting through edits); code file; code snapshot (a commit-anchored state of an entity carrying volatile facts: content hash, line span, metrics); code role (an anti-rigid role an entity plays — core algorithm, domain logic, boundary, glue, boilerplate, generated); criticality (an axis orthogonal to role); attention policy (a function of role, criticality and observations together); observation (a measured, instrument-provenanced, append-only occurrent anchored to a snapshot — performance profile, change churn and authorship concentration, defect attribution, verification state); authorship provenance (whether a human or a specific agent authored a region).

Core relationships: an entity is declared in a file (physical containment: directory/file) and sits in a logical module/item hierarchy — two distinct containment hierarchies crossed by declaredIn, never merged. Entities call, use, implement and access one another, and expose public API, FFI, or network entry points. An entity plays a role via a playing-relation that carries lifecycle status and ratification provenance — never role-as-subclass: an entity IS a function and PLAYS core algorithm. Refactor continuity is typed edges: renamedFrom, movedFrom, splitInto, mergedInto. Observations attach to snapshots, never directly to entities; nothing is anchored by line number except snapshot data. Code links upward into architecture and knowledge: an entity realizes a system component, satisfies a requirement, embodies a pattern; constraints constrain code entities and anti-patterns are violated by them.

Discipline: three strata with distinct change semantics — structure (derived from source, regenerated per commit, never hand-asserted), judgments (proposed from evidence, human-ratified, lifecycle-managed), observations (measured, append-only). Shape validation should differ per stratum. Keep the taxonomy shallow and the lexical surface rich..
Core fallback: yes.
Mid-level clustering disabled.""" .

# =============================================================================
# Annotation Property Definitions
# =============================================================================

trivyn:confidence a owl:AnnotationProperty ;
    rdfs:label "confidence score" ;
    rdfs:comment "Confidence score for automated alignments and equivalences (0.0-1.0)" ;
    rdfs:range xsd:decimal .

# =============================================================================
# v2.0 core — CodeEntity (structure stratum; derived from the substrate index,
# never hand-asserted; identity per AD 136dbf24, normalization per Constraint
# 00b3986e)
# =============================================================================

:CodeEntity a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Code Entity" ;
    skos:definition "A named, addressable source-code continuant — a module, function, method, type, trait, constant, or other declared symbol — identified by its substrate symbol (a normalized SCIP symbol, or a syntactic anchor for fallback-resolved languages) and persisting through edits, renames, and moves. A referent that records are about, not itself an information record: it carries no author, timestamp, or lifecycle status. Nothing about it is anchored by line number." ;
    trivyn:labelProperty :hasCodeName ;
    skos:historyNote "Derived from synthesis source 'CodeEntity'" ;
    rdfs:subClassOf se:Component {| skos:historyNote "Hand-curated 2026-07-08: ratified Component/Module lineage per AD b0d3e4d9; the generated arch:SystemComponent bridge (0.75) was overruled" |} .

# Datatype Properties (all domain :CodeEntity, range xsd:string)
:hasSubstrateSymbol a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "has substrate symbol" ;
    rdfs:domain :CodeEntity ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string ;
    skos:definition "The substrate symbol string that is the entity's identity key. For SCIP-resolved entities: the normalized SCIP symbol, version descriptor elided (Constraint 00b3986e) so identity survives version bumps. For fallback-resolved entities: a syntactic anchor of the form ts:<lang>:<repo-relative-path>:<kind>:<qualified-name>. Exactly one per entity; no two entities share one." ;
    skos:historyNote "Hand-curated 2026-07-08 from generated 'hasSymbolPath' (ratified name, slice-2 Phase 0 worksheet)" ;
    skos:editorialNote "Renamed from hasScipSymbol 2026-07-10 (slice-4 Phase 0): the tree-sitter fallback introduces non-SCIP identities and the identity property must not lie about its value space. Graph migrated via examples/migrate_substrate_symbol.rs." ;
    rdfs:subPropertyOf cco:ont00001765 {| trivyn:confidence "0.85"^^xsd:decimal ; trivyn:parentLabel "has text value" ; skos:historyNote "Aligned to has text value via embedding similarity" ; dcterms:created "2026-07-08T05:46:40Z"^^xsd:dateTime |} .

:hasEntityKind a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "has entity kind" ;
    rdfs:domain :CodeEntity ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string ;
    skos:definition "The structural kind reported by the index producer: Module, Function, Struct, Trait, Method, Enum, Constant, and similar. A datatype property, not a class hierarchy — the kind taxonomy belongs to the producer, not the ontology." ;
    skos:historyNote "Hand-curated 2026-07-08 (ratified worksheet; replaces the generated CodeKind class + categorizes property)" .

:hasCodeName a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "has code name" ;
    rdfs:domain :CodeEntity ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string ;
    skos:definition "The entity's human-readable name as written in source; the label property of CodeEntity." ;
    skos:historyNote "Hand-curated 2026-07-08 (ratified worksheet)" .

:hasLogicalPath a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "has logical path" ;
    rdfs:domain :CodeEntity ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string ;
    skos:definition "The qualified logical path of the entity within the crate/module hierarchy, e.g. 'runtime::build_server'." ;
    skos:historyNote "Hand-curated 2026-07-08 (ratified worksheet)" .

:definedInPath a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "defined in path" ;
    rdfs:domain :CodeEntity ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string ;
    skos:definition "The repo-relative path of the defining source file — physical containment. A path, never a line number; regenerated from the substrate index, not hand-asserted." ;
    skos:historyNote "Hand-curated 2026-07-08 (ratified worksheet)" .

# Object Properties — upward intent links (AD 7079634f): the code layer joins
# the record layer into one graph. Ranges are architecture-ontology classes;
# subject-side legality comes from CodeEntityShape in software-code_shapes.ttl.
# Reuse note: an entity violating a constraint uses the (widened) architecture
# property arch:violates — the relation is the same one anti-patterns use.
:realizes a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:label "realizes" ;
    rdfs:domain :CodeEntity ;
    rdfs:range <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#SystemComponent> ;
    owl:inverseOf :isRealizedBy ;
    skos:definition "Relates a code entity to the system component it realizes; records concerning the component transitively concern its realizing code. Derived from the component path map (coversPath) at mint time." ;
    skos:historyNote "Hand-curated 2026-07-08 (ratified worksheet, AD 7079634f)" .

:isRealizedBy a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:label "is realized by" ;
    owl:inverseOf :realizes ;
    rdfs:domain <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#SystemComponent> ;
    rdfs:range :CodeEntity ;
    skos:definition "Relates a system component to a code entity that realizes it." ;
    skos:historyNote "Hand-curated 2026-07-08 (ratified worksheet, AD 7079634f)" .

:satisfies a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:label "satisfies" ;
    rdfs:domain :CodeEntity ;
    rdfs:range <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Requirement> ;
    owl:inverseOf :isSatisfiedBy ;
    skos:definition "Relates a code entity to a requirement it satisfies." ;
    skos:historyNote "Hand-curated 2026-07-08 (ratified worksheet, AD 7079634f)" .

:isSatisfiedBy a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:label "is satisfied by" ;
    owl:inverseOf :satisfies ;
    rdfs:domain <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Requirement> ;
    rdfs:range :CodeEntity ;
    skos:definition "Relates a requirement to a code entity that satisfies it." ;
    skos:historyNote "Hand-curated 2026-07-08 (ratified worksheet, AD 7079634f)" .

:embodies a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:label "embodies" ;
    rdfs:domain :CodeEntity ;
    rdfs:range <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Pattern> ;
    owl:inverseOf :isEmbodiedBy ;
    skos:definition "Relates a code entity to a pattern it embodies." ;
    skos:historyNote "Hand-curated 2026-07-08 (ratified worksheet, AD 7079634f)" .

:isEmbodiedBy a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:label "is embodied by" ;
    owl:inverseOf :embodies ;
    rdfs:domain <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/architecture#Pattern> ;
    rdfs:range :CodeEntity ;
    skos:definition "Relates a pattern to a code entity that embodies it." ;
    skos:historyNote "Hand-curated 2026-07-08 (ratified worksheet, AD 7079634f)" .

# Object Properties — judgment stratum playing-relations (spec §3.4). The edge
# itself is plain and queryable; its lifecycle status, confidence, evidence,
# and ratification provenance live on the resolved ProposedLink node that
# proposed it (the reify-as-node discipline). Materialized only on human
# acceptance — a proposed judgment has no edge. No owl:inverseOf on purpose:
# a declared inverse would make enrichment materialize hub edges on the few
# role/criticality individuals, one per accepted judgment, for a direction
# nothing reads.
:playsRole a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:label "plays role" ;
    rdfs:domain :CodeEntity ;
    rdfs:range :CodeRole ;
    skos:definition "Relates a code entity to the anti-rigid functional role it plays (an entity IS a function and PLAYS core algorithm — never role-as-subclass). Human-ratified: asserted only by accepting a judgment proposal; the accepted proposal node carries the ratification provenance." ;
    skos:historyNote "Introduced with the judgment stratum (role/criticality classifier slice); taxonomy per AD b5b4762b" .

:hasCriticality a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:label "has criticality" ;
    rdfs:domain :CodeEntity ;
    rdfs:range :Criticality ;
    skos:definition "Relates a code entity to its criticality — the cost of it being wrong, an axis orthogonal to role. Only deviations from the derived default (standard) are asserted; human-ratified via the judgment queue like playsRole." ;
    skos:historyNote "Introduced with the judgment stratum (role/criticality classifier slice)" .

# =============================================================================
# Ratification queue — v2.1 ambient layer, extended by the judgment stratum.
# A ProposedLink is a pending, human-ratifiable proposal for one edge. Two
# kinds share the node shape: (a) record→entity links (v2.1: subject record +
# predicate + target substrate symbol, materialized via link_code) and
# (b) judgments (entity subject + playsRole/hasCriticality + proposesTargetIri
# naming a role/criticality individual, plus confidence and escalation,
# materialized via relate()). It carries the proposed triple as LITERALS
# (never the real edge), so an unratified proposal is invisible to dossier
# edges, the gate, and the why-coverage metric until accepted; rejection only
# flips status. The resolved node is preserved as the edge's ratification
# provenance. Deliberately NOT an InformationRecord subclass (stays out of
# record listings + the ABox vector index) and given NO SHACL shape (no
# relation-catalogue write path — the proposal literals are written directly,
# not oriented through relate()).
# =============================================================================

:ProposedLink a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Proposed Link" ;
    skos:definition "A pending, human-ratifiable proposal for one edge: an information record linking to a code entity (link kind), or a code entity playing a role / carrying a criticality (judgment kind). Carries the proposed triple as literals plus a lifecycle status; the real edge exists only after ratification, and the resolved node remains as its ratification provenance. Not an information record and not the edge itself — a queue entry." ;
    skos:historyNote "Introduced v2.1 (ambient layer + ratification inbox); first written by the citation-seed migration. Extended to judgment proposals (proposesTargetIri/hasConfidence/hasEscalation) by the judgment-stratum slice." .

# Datatype Properties (all domain :ProposedLink, range xsd:string) — the proposed
# triple stored as literals so no real link edge exists until acceptance.
:proposesSubject a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "proposes subject" ;
    rdfs:domain :ProposedLink ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string ;
    skos:definition "The IRI (as a literal string, never an edge) of the information record the proposal would link from." ;
    skos:historyNote "Introduced v2.1" .

:proposesPredicate a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "proposes predicate" ;
    rdfs:domain :ProposedLink ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string ;
    skos:definition "The local name of the link predicate to assert on acceptance (e.g. 'concerns', 'satisfies')." ;
    skos:historyNote "Introduced v2.1" .

:proposesTargetSymbol a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "proposes target symbol" ;
    rdfs:domain :ProposedLink ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string ;
    skos:definition "The substrate symbol of the target code entity, resolved at HEAD; re-resolved via link_code on acceptance so a symbol that no longer exists fails honestly." ;
    skos:historyNote "Introduced v2.1" .

:proposesTargetPath a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "proposes target path" ;
    rdfs:domain :ProposedLink ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string ;
    skos:definition "The repo-relative path of the target entity's defining file, for display and the migration report." ;
    skos:historyNote "Introduced v2.1" .

:proposesTargetIri a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "proposes target IRI" ;
    rdfs:domain :ProposedLink ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string ;
    skos:definition "The IRI (as a literal string, never an edge) of the proposal's target individual — a CodeRole or Criticality — for judgment-kind proposals. Its presence is what distinguishes a judgment from a link proposal; acceptance materializes the edge via relate() with no symbol resolution." ;
    skos:historyNote "Introduced by the judgment-stratum slice" .

:hasConfidence a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "has confidence" ;
    rdfs:domain :ProposedLink ;
    rdfs:range xsd:decimal ;
    skos:definition "The classifier's confidence (0.0–1.0) in a judgment-kind proposal, from the emitting rule's calibrated constant. Advisory surfaces display it; it never gates." ;
    skos:historyNote "Introduced by the judgment-stratum slice (confidence gate, Consequence be097082)" .

:hasEscalation a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "has escalation" ;
    rdfs:domain :ProposedLink ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string ;
    skos:definition "The confidence-gate disposition of a judgment-kind proposal: 'escalated' (low confidence or high stakes — shown first in the inbox) or 'auto-held' (high confidence, low stakes — waits quietly). Inbox prominence only: no judgment proposal ever counts toward the pending-ratifications nudge." ;
    skos:historyNote "Introduced by the judgment-stratum slice (never-nudge amendment of Consequence be097082, sanctioned 2026-07-13)" .

# =============================================================================
# Parked stratum classes — names ratified in the 2026-07-03 alignment pass
# (AD b0d3e4d9); declared for name stability only. NO properties and NO shapes
# until the owning stratum's machinery ships (judgments: v2.1 ratification
# inbox; observations: v2.2 instrumentation), so they create no write paths.
# =============================================================================

:CodeFile a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Code File" ;
    skos:definition "A physical storage unit within a directory hierarchy that contains source code content. Physical containment is a distinct hierarchy from the logical module hierarchy; the two are crossed, never merged." ;
    skos:historyNote "Derived from synthesis source 'CodeFile'; parked for v2.1+. Generated alignment ⊑ se:Module overruled 2026-07-08 (a file is not a module)" .

:CodeSnapshot a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Code Snapshot" ;
    skos:definition "A commit-anchored state of a code entity representing a specific point in time with volatile metrics and content hashes." ;
    skos:historyNote "Derived from synthesis source 'CodeSnapshot'; parked for v2.1+" ;
    rdfs:subClassOf cco:ont00000958 {| trivyn:confidence "0.40"^^xsd:decimal ; trivyn:l0Category "record" ; trivyn:parentLabel "Information Content Entity" ; trivyn:tierFallback "true"^^xsd:boolean ; skos:historyNote "Aligned to Information Content Entity via embedding similarity" ; skos:editorialNote "Tier-root fallback — L3 abstained; parent is the L0 category tier root" ; dcterms:created "2026-07-08T05:46:40Z"^^xsd:dateTime |} .

:CodeRole a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Code Role" ;
    skos:definition "An anti-rigid functional role played by a code entity within the system's logic (core algorithm, domain logic, boundary, glue, boilerplate, generated — taxonomy per AD b5b4762b). An entity IS a function and PLAYS a role; never role-as-subclass." ;
    skos:historyNote "Derived from synthesis source 'CodeRole'; UN-PARKED by the judgment-stratum slice: the playing-relation is playsRole, whose lifecycle status and ratification provenance live on the accepting ProposedLink node. Taxonomy individuals are deterministic project-graph instances (https://moosedev.dev/kg/CodeRole/<role>)" ;
    rdfs:subClassOf obo:BFO_0000023 {| trivyn:confidence "0.60"^^xsd:decimal ; trivyn:l0Category "role" ; trivyn:parentLabel "role" ; skos:historyNote "Aligned to role via embedding similarity" ; dcterms:created "2026-07-08T05:46:40Z"^^xsd:dateTime |} .

:Criticality a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Criticality" ;
    skos:definition "An axis orthogonal to role measuring the cost of a code entity being wrong." ;
    skos:historyNote "Derived from synthesis source 'Criticality'; UN-PARKED by the judgment-stratum slice via hasCriticality (individuals high/standard/low; standard is the implicit derived default and never asserted)" ;
    rdfs:subClassOf obo:BFO_0000019 {| trivyn:confidence "0.60"^^xsd:decimal ; trivyn:l0Category "attribute" ; trivyn:parentLabel "quality" ; skos:historyNote "Aligned to quality via embedding similarity" ; dcterms:created "2026-07-08T05:46:40Z"^^xsd:dateTime |} .

:AttentionPolicy a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Attention Policy" ;
    skos:definition "A derived governance rule determined by the intersection of role, criticality, and observations — never a function of role alone." ;
    skos:historyNote "Derived from synthesis source 'AttentionPolicy'; parked for v2.1+. Generated alignment ⊑ arch:Constraint overruled 2026-07-08 (a derived policy is not a constraint record)" .

:Observation a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Observation" ;
    skos:definition "An append-only, instrument-provenanced measurement anchored to a specific code snapshot — performance, churn, defect attribution, verification state." ;
    skos:historyNote "Derived from synthesis source 'Observation'; parked for v2.2 instrumentation" ;
    rdfs:subClassOf cco:ont00000958 {| trivyn:confidence "0.40"^^xsd:decimal ; trivyn:l0Category "record" ; trivyn:parentLabel "Information Content Entity" ; trivyn:tierFallback "true"^^xsd:boolean ; skos:historyNote "Aligned to Information Content Entity via embedding similarity" ; skos:editorialNote "Tier-root fallback — L3 abstained; parent is the L0 category tier root" ; dcterms:created "2026-07-08T05:46:40Z"^^xsd:dateTime |} .

:AuthorshipProvenance a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Authorship Provenance" ;
    skos:definition "The attribution of authorship to a specific human or agent for a region of code." ;
    skos:historyNote "Derived from synthesis source 'AuthorshipProvenance'; parked for v2.2. Generated alignment ⊑ se:ExternalDependency overruled 2026-07-08 (semantically wrong); expected to reuse the existing PROV provenance machinery when designed" .

# =============================================================================
# End of Domain Ontology
# =============================================================================

# Competency questions this ontology was built to answer (synthesis).
<https://trivyn.io/ontologies/software/code>
    <https://trivyn.io/ontologies/toekg#satisfiesCompetencyQuestion> "Which code entities playing a 'core algorithm' role have high criticality and high defect attribution observations?",
        "How has the structural composition of a specific module changed across different code snapshots?",
        "Which requirements are currently satisfied by the existing code entities in a specific component?",
        "What is the authorship concentration for entities identified as 'glue' code?",
        "Which code entities are currently violating defined architectural constraints?" .

